latestPosts.caption:
Darjeeling through my lens. 

It used to be everything. You’d walk those sloped roads like they were stitched to your feet — every shortcut, every crack in the wall and laughter from my school friends made every narrow lane feel like it belonged to me.

Things change when you leave. When you return, the roads look the same, but your footsteps don’t quite echo like they used to. Stores have changed. People have grown. The sky is still breathtaking, but it doesn’t pull the same breath from you. Now, you’re a visitor in your own story — warmly welcomed, deeply missed, but slightly out of rhythm.

But you still love it, maybe even more. Because it’s still home. Just one that doesn’t wait for me anymore. 🤍

#darjeelingdiaries🏔️ #ilovedarjeeling #darjeelingtips #explorepage #exploremore
